{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb911a0a5-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8703"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8703"},"text":"§ 8703.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Benefit certificate","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Office of Personnel Management shall arrange to have each insured employee receive a certificate setting forth the benefits to which he is entitled, to whom the benefits are payable, to whom the claims shall be submitted, and summarizing the provisions of the policy principally affecting him. The certificate is issued instead of the certificate which the insurance company would otherwise be required to issue.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb911a0a6-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/554"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–554","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/593"},"text":"80 Stat. 593","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454/tIX/s906/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454, title IX, § 906(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1224"},"text":"92 Stat. 1224","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb911a0a7-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb911a0a8-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idb911a0a9-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"